#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/js-batch-dom-css.md
M|rules|title: Avoid Layout Thrashing
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: prevents forced synchronous layouts and reduces performance bottlenecks
M|rules|tags: javascript, dom, css, performance, reflow, layout-thrashing
M|rules|Avoid interleaving style writes with layout reads. When you read a layout property (like `offsetWidth`, `getBoundingClientRect()`, or `getComputedStyle()`) between style changes, the browser is forced
M|rules|**This is OK (browser batches style changes):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function updateElementStyles(element: HTMLElement) {
M|rules|// Each line invalidates style, but browser batches the recalculation
M|rules|element.style.width = '100px'
M|rules|element.style.height = '200px'
M|rules|element.style.backgroundColor = 'blue'
M|rules|element.style.border = '1px solid black'
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Incorrect (interleaved reads and writes force reflows):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function layoutThrashing(element: HTMLElement) {
M|rules|element.style.width = '100px'
M|rules|const width = element.offsetWidth  // Forces reflow
M|rules|element.style.height = '200px'
M|rules|const height = element.offsetHeight  // Forces another reflow
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (batch writes, then read once):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function updateElementStyles(element: HTMLElement) {
M|rules|// Batch all writes together
M|rules|element.style.width = '100px'
M|rules|element.style.height = '200px'
M|rules|element.style.backgroundColor = 'blue'
M|rules|element.style.border = '1px solid black'
M|rules|// Read after all writes are done (single reflow)
M|rules|const { width, height } = element.getBoundingClientRect()
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (batch reads, then writes):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function avoidThrashing(element: HTMLElement) {
M|rules|// Read phase - all layout queries first
M|rules|const rect1 = element.getBoundingClientRect()
M|rules|const offsetWidth = element.offsetWidth
M|rules|const offsetHeight = element.offsetHeight
M|rules|// Write phase - all style changes after
M|rules|element.style.width = '100px'
M|rules|element.style.height = '200px'
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Better: use CSS classes**
M|rules|```css
M|rules|.highlighted-box {
M|rules|width: 100px;
M|rules|height: 200px;
M|rules|background-color: blue;
M|rules|border: 1px solid black;
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function updateElementStyles(element: HTMLElement) {
M|rules|element.classList.add('highlighted-box')
M|rules|const { width, height } = element.getBoundingClientRect()
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**React example:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// Incorrect: interleaving style changes with layout queries
M|rules|function Box({ isHighlighted }: { isHighlighted: boolean }) {
M|rules|const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null)
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|if (ref.current && isHighlighted) {
M|rules|ref.current.style.width = '100px'
M|rules|const width = ref.current.offsetWidth // Forces layout
M|rules|ref.current.style.height = '200px'
M|rules|}
M|rules|}, [isHighlighted])
M|rules|return <div ref={ref}>cnt</div>
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Correct: toggle class
M|rules|function Box({ isHighlighted }: { isHighlighted: boolean }) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<div className={isHighlighted ? 'highlighted-box' : ''}>
M|rules|cnt
M|rules|</div>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Prefer CSS classes over inline styles when possible. CSS files are cached by the browser, and classes provide better separation of concerns and are easier to maintain.
M|rules|See [this gist](https://gist.github.com/paulirish/5d52fb081b3570c81e3a) and [CSS Triggers](https://csstriggers.com/) for more information on layout-forcing operations.